      <sectiondef kind="func">
      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__SL__PING__FUNCTIONS_1gabe41d48d834975a419264388851c40ff" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>sl_status_t</type>
        <definition>sl_status_t sl_si91x_send_ping</definition>
        <argsstring>(sl_ip_address_t ip_address, uint16_t ping_packet_size)</argsstring>
        <name>sl_si91x_send_ping</name>
        <param>
          <type>sl_ip_address_t</type>
          <declname>ip_address</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>uint16_t</type>
          <declname>ping_packet_size</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Send an ICMP ping request to a specific IP address. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function sends an ICMP ping request to a specific IP address (IPv4 or IPv6) with a user defined ping packet size. It verifies the device’s initialization status and validates the IP address type before sending the request to the specific IP address. <simplesect kind="pre"><para>Pre-condition:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><ulink url="../wiseconnect-api-reference-guide-nwk-mgmt/net-interface-functions#sl-net-up">sl_net_up</ulink> should be called before this API. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">ip_address</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The destination IP address should be of type <ulink url="../wiseconnect-api-reference-guide-common/sl-ip-address-t">sl_ip_address_type_t</ulink> either IPv4 or IPv6. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">ping_packet_size</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The size of the ping packet must fall within the valid range of [0, 300]. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><ulink url="https://docs.silabs.com/gecko-platform/latest/platform-common/status">sl_status_t</ulink> - Status of the operation.<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>SL_STATUS_OK: Operation successful.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>SL_STATUS_NOT_INITIALIZED: Device is not initialized.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>SL_STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER: Invalid IP address type.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>This API is asynchronous. The ping response is delivered through the registered <ulink url="../wiseconnect-api-reference-guide-nwk-mgmt/sl-net-types#sl-net-event-handler-t">sl_net_event_handler_t</ulink> callback, using the event type <ulink url="../wiseconnect-api-reference-guide-nwk-mgmt/sl-net-constants#sl-net-event-t">SL_NET_PING_RESPONSE_EVENT</ulink>. To receive this event, the sl_net_event_handler_t must be registered via the <ulink url="../wiseconnect-api-reference-guide-nwk-mgmt/net-interface-functions#sl-net-init">sl_net_init()</ulink> API. </para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
